An unidentified man sustained injuries while four families escaped unhurt after a two-storey building collapsed in Lagos in the wee hours of  yesterday. The incident occurred at 15 Oke Arin Street in Ilupeju around 12:40am. Barely two weeks ago, a church building under construction collapsed in Mushin, Lagos.   Lagos Assembly denies passing Sharia law     Court rules today on Oyo deputy governor’s impeachment     Why LASUTH is helping Nigeria address shortage of…   Four families in the Ilupeju building took to their heels when they heard cracking sounds from the old building before it collapsed. Emergency workers cordoned off the place. However, the families who fled were seen rummaging the debris in search of their belongings. Permanent Secretary, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA), Dr. Femi Oke-Osanyintolu, said the injured man was taken to hospital. Oke-Osanyintolu said: “Fortunately, no loss of life. However, one adult male sustained minor injury and has been taken to hospital.”